DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: _The movement of one cell type into an area normally occupied by a different cell type:The space in the eye, filled with aqueous humor, bounded anteriorly by the cornea and a small portion of the sclera and posteriorly by a small portion of the ciliary body, the iris, and that part of the crystalline lens which presents through the pupil. (Cline et al., Dictionary of Visual Science, 4th ed, p109)_Being or existing in a specified place or at the specified time.
